me.timothy.tests.database

Class BannedUserMappingTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.timothy.tests.database.BannedUserMappingTest
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    MysqlBannedUserMappingTest

    public class BannedUserMappingTest
extends java.lang.Object
    Describes tests focused on testing an BannedUserMapping inside a MappingDatabase. The database should be completely empty before each test. The database will be modified. This should not be run against a production database.
    Author:
    Timothy

      • testSave

        public void testSave()

        Tests the ability to save BannedUsers

        This is a basic test to ensure that doing a standard save does not result in any errors, and sets the id of the user to the database, and the very same BannedUser is returned, compared with equals, fetched with fetchAll

        This has the side-effect of checking BannedUsers equals function is implemented.
